body:
When compiling on Windows as of d6126c4b3, I am getting errors due to a namespace collision for the symbol `CONTEXT` due to a system header:

```
../V3Width.cpp:99:5: error: 'CONTEXT' redeclared as different kind of entity
   99 |     CONTEXT,  // Context-determined
      |     ^~~~~~~
In file included from C:/msys64/mingw64/include/minwindef.h:163,
                 from C:/msys64/mingw64/include/windef.h:9,
                 from C:/msys64/mingw64/include/Windows.h:69,
                 from ../../include/verilatedos.h:475:
C:/msys64/mingw64/include/winnt.h:1878:5: note: previous declaration 'typedef struct _CONTEXT CONTEXT'
 1878 |   } CONTEXT,*PCONTEXT;
``` 

This PR changes the name to `CONTEXT_DET` for the sake of avoiding conflicts with system headers, now that the new thread-safe-by-default behavior brings in more headers.

